DTSTAMP:20260325T063303Z
DTSTART:20260401T171500Z
DESCRIPTION:Wednesday\, April 1\, 2026\, 10:15 - 10:45am\n\nAt storytime\, 
	kids ages 0-5 and their families can enjoy stories\, songs\, and fun learn
	ing activities.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nFremont Branch\n\nRegistration Requir
	ed: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: Early Learning 
	is a great way for kids ages 0-5 and their families to develop learning\, 
	literacy\, and language skills as well as community with other families.\,
	 We read stories\, sing songs\, and have engaging\, educational activities
	 that help kids and their caregivers grow together.\n\nEvent Logistics: Re
	gistration is not required but these programs are very popular and the roo
	m capacity can fill up quickly.\, Families of all ages are welcome\, thoug
	h this early learning program is intended for youth aged 0-5\, their careg
	ivers and families.\, Doors to the meeting room will open at 10:00 am. Ent
	rance to the meeting room from the Library is down a flight of stairs. A s
	troller-friendly entrance is through the park next to the Library.\, Find 
	out more about\n\nEarly Learning & Story Time\n\nprograms.\n\nContact Us: 
